title: 'Strange metals' point to a whole new way to understand electricity
author: pseudolus
summary: Strange metals are a class of materials that behave differently from ordinary metals and challenge existing theories of electricity. Recent research suggests that in these materials, electrons lose their individuality and may act as a collective "soup" rather than distinct particles. Understanding strange metals could lead to breakthroughs in superconductivity and new ways to think about electricity.
recommendation: 文章介绍了奇异金属这一前沿科学领域的研究进展，提供了关于电子行为的新见解，挑战了传统理论，具有较高的科学价值和潜在应用前景。

title: Design Pressure: The Invisible Hand That Shapes Your Code
author: NeutralForest
summary: The author discusses the feeling that something might be wrong with your code, even when following best practices. They highlight the challenges of maintaining good architecture in software projects. The text also references various resources, including articles, videos, and books related to software design.
recommendation: 文章触及了软件开发中常见的直觉性焦虑问题，并提供了相关资源链接，对开发者心理和架构维护有实际参考价值，但深度和独特性有限。

title: "The American Dream 2025" Elderly Walmart employee on a COPD machine and crying
author: dp-hackernews
summary: Many elderly Americans are struggling to retire due to healthcare costs and financial insecurity. Comments on social media highlight the sadness and fear surrounding retirement for future generations. The situation reflects a larger issue of poverty and inadequate support systems for the aging population in the U.S.
recommendation: 文章揭示了美国老年人面临的退休困境，特别是医疗费用和财务不安全感，这些信息对于理解社会福利体系的不足和潜在改革需求具有价值。虽然未提供具体数据或解决方案，但引发了关于老龄化社会问题的思考。

title: Show HN: Wall Go – browser remake of a Devil's Plan 2 mini-game
author: sychu
summary:
Source code: https://github.com/schaoss/wall-goI binge-watched Netflix’s “Devil’s Plan 2” and got hooked on the “Wall Go” round.  
A few nights of vibe-coding later, here’s a fully playable browser version:• 7×7 board, staggered placement (1-2-2-1), 0-to-2-step moves, mandatory wall each turn.
• Light / dark mode, mobile-friendly hit boxes  
• Simple AI (ΔReach + liberty heuristic) – beats random, not a grandmaster yet  
• Tech stack: Bun + Vite + React + Tailwind v4 + Zustand, deployed on GitHub PagesLooking for feedback:
* is the AI too weak / unfair?  
* any UI quirks on touch devices?  
* rule misinterpretations I missed?Bug reports, feature requests, or PRs very welcome.  
Hope you enjoy boxing your friends into tiny corners as much as I did while coding this :)

Comments URL: https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=44088248
Points: 3
# Comments: 0
recommendation: 文章展示了一个基于热门综艺开发的游戏原型，提供了完整的开源代码和技术栈细节，对开发者有直接参考价值；AI设计部分虽简单但启发性强，适合技术爱好者复现或改进。
